* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/ˈaɪ.kən/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/ˈaɪ.kɑːn/}}
** {{audio|en|En-us-icon.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[Image:Cyril_Methodius25K.jpg|right|thumb|160px|A religious icon]]

# An [[image]], [[symbol]], [[picture]], or other [[representation]] usually as an object of religious devotion.
# {{lb|en|religion|especially|Eastern Christianity}} A type of religious painting portraying a [[saint]] or scene from [[Scripture]], often done on wooden panels.
# A person or thing that is the best example of a certain profession or some doing.
#: ''That man is an '''icon''' in the business; he personifies loyalty and good business sense.''
# {{lb|en|computing}} A small picture that represents something (such as an icon on a computer screen which when clicked performs some function.)
# {{lb|en|linguistics}} A word, character, or sign whose form reflects and is determined by the [[referent]]; [[onomatopoeic]] words are necessarily all icons. See also {{m|en|symbol}} and {{m|en|index}}.

